articles.description: Tevon Saddler and Roddy Peters scored 15 points apiece, and Nicholls held on to beat Sam Houston State 73-72 on Wednesday night for its fourth straight win.
articles.headline: Nicholls holds off Sam Houston State 73-72

articles.description: Aaron Cook sank two free throws with four seconds remaining in overtime, Armon Fletcher scored 22 points and Southern Illinois turned back Missouri State 81-80 Wednesday night, running its record to 7-1 over the last eight games.
articles.headline: Cook late FTs lift S. Illinois over Missouri St. 81-80, OT

articles.description: Forward Yante Maten earns his tenth double-double to push the Bulldogs to a dramatic road win over the Gators.
articles.headline: UGA squeaks past Florida in OT 72-69

images.caption: Forward Yante Maten earns his tenth double-double to push the Bulldogs to a dramatic road win over the Gators.
images.name: UGA squeaks past Florida in OT 72-69

articles.description: Jaron Hopkins scored 16 of his 20 points in the second half when Deshon Taylor scored 12 of his 19 and Fresno State pulled away for a 77-57 win over San Jose State on Wednesday night.
articles.headline: Hopkins, Taylor lead Fresno State past San Jose State 77-57

articles.description: Yante Maten scored 23 points, including a huge 3-pointer to send the game into overtime, and Georgia beat Florida 72-69 Wednesday night to end a three-game losing streak in Southeastern Conference play.
articles.headline: Maten scores 23, Georgia sweeps Florida with 72-69 OT win

images.caption: Forward Yante Maten earns his tenth double-double to push the Bulldogs to a dramatic road win over the Gators.
images.name: UGA squeaks past Florida in OT 72-69

articles.description: Georgia head coach Mark Fox talks about the Bulldogs' comeback win over the Gators and the contributions of senior Yante Maten.
articles.headline: Fox: 'Maten is a winner'

videos.description: Nick Weatherspoon comes over on help defense and gets a block for the Bulldogs.
videos.headline: Mississippi State's Weatherspoon swats away dunk attempt

videos.description: Lamar Peters displays brilliant open court play, with a steal and open court layup for the Bulldogs.
videos.headline: Mississippi State's Peters gets a steal and score

videos.description: Tyson Carter goes through two defenders, and  scores an up-tempo layup for the Bulldogs and is foul for a three-point play.
videos.headline: Mississippi State's Carter scores acrobatic basket for and-1

videos.description: Daniel Gafford gets the pass from Daryl Macon and dunks home an easy finish for the Bulldogs.
videos.headline: Arkansas' Gafford scores with a two-handed flush

videos.description: Anton Beard hits a 3-pointer for the Razorbacks to cap an 8-0 run in the second half.
videos.headline: Arkansas' Beard drains a 3-pointer in rhythm

videos.description: Daniel Gafford catches and jams the alley-oop feed from Anton Beard for the Razorbacks.
videos.headline: Arkansas' Beard, Gafford connect for alley-oop jam

videos.description: Anton Beard drives the lane and scores a basket off the glass for the Razorbacks.
videos.headline: Beard kisses one off glass for a basket

videos.description: Xavian Stapleton scores a right-handed layup and is fouled for an old-fashioned 3-point play.
videos.headline: Mississippi State's Stapleton scores layup for and-1

videos.description: Jaylen Barford's in bounds bounce pass finds Adrio Bailey for a thunderous two-handed slam for the Razorbacks.
videos.headline: Arkansas' Barford, Bailey connect for dunk off the inbound pass

videos.description: Nick Weatherspoon score a transition Eurostep jumper for the Bulldogs to tie the game late in the second half.
videos.headline: Mississippi State's Weatherspoon Eurosteps for a jumper

videos.description: Daryl Macon hits a deep 3-pointer for the Razorbacks and is foul for the rare 4-point play.
videos.headline: Macon hits from downtown and gets fouled

videos.description: Adrio Bailey steals the cross-court pass and runs the floor to score an easy layup to give the Razorbacks the lead.
videos.headline: Bailey's brilliant plays leads to bucket

videos.description: Quinndary Weatherspoon hits his second 3-pointer of the game to tie it late for the Bulldogs.
videos.headline: Weatherspoon swishes step-back 3-pointer to tie the game

videos.description: Quinndary Weatherspoon says defense was the key in the Bulldogs 78-75 victory over Arkansas.
videos.headline: Weatherspoon credits defense for gutty win

videos.description: Abdul Ado wins the fight for the loose ball and scores a layup off glass to give the Bulldogs the lead late.
videos.headline: Ado wins the 50/50 ball and scores layup

videos.description: The Bulldogs shoot 40 free throws en route to a win and move to 13-1 on the season.
videos.headline: Mississippi State defeats No. 22 Arkansas 78-75
